<doc id="44193" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=44193" title="Discovery going for second launch since 2003 Columbia loss">
<h1>Discovery going for second launch since 2003 Columbia loss</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Discovery%20going%20for%20second%20launch%20since%202003%20Columbia%20loss&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

With a planned launch time of 3:48 &lt;a href="w%3AEastern_Daylight_Time"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt; (19:48 &lt;a href="w%3ACoordinated_Universal_Time"&gt;UTC&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href="w%3ANASA"&gt;NASA's&lt;/a&gt; shuttle &lt;a href="w%3ASpace_Shuttle_Discovery"&gt;Discovery&lt;/a&gt; embarks on the second mission since the loss of shuttle Columbia in 2003. The mission designation is &lt;a href="w%3ASTS-121"&gt;STS-121&lt;/a&gt;.

The crew are as follows:
<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3ASteven%20W.%20Lindsey"&gt;Steven W. Lindsey&lt;/a&gt; - Commander - USA
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3AMark%20E.%20Kelly"&gt;Mark E. Kelly&lt;/a&gt; - Pilot - USA
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3AMichael%20E.%20Fossum"&gt;Michael E. Fossum&lt;/a&gt; - Mission Specialist - USA
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3ALisa%20Nowak"&gt;Lisa Nowak&lt;/a&gt; - Mission Specialist - USA
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3AStephanie%20Wilson"&gt;Stephanie Wilson&lt;/a&gt; - Mission Specialist - USA
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3APiers%20Sellers"&gt;Piers Sellers&lt;/a&gt; - Mission Specialist - USA
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="w%3AThomas%20Reiter"&gt;Thomas Reiter&lt;/a&gt; - Astronaut - European Space Agency

</ul>
As of 3:50 PM EDT (19:50 UTC), the weather has delayed the launch until July 2, with a planned launch time of 3:26 PM EDT (19:26 GMT).

