<doc id="44196" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=44196" title="Superman returns to theatres">
<h1>Superman returns to theatres</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Superman%20returns%20to%20theatres&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;a href="w%3ASuperman"&gt;Superman&lt;/a&gt; returned to theatres for the first time in nearly 20 years, when ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3ASuperman%20Returns"&gt;Superman Returns&lt;/a&gt;♡❤ opened on Wednesday. The film earned $21 million on its first day of showing, making it the eighth biggest box-office draw ever for a Wednesday opening in North America.

The film has so far received generally positive reviews from the media. It is directed by &lt;a href="w%3ABryan%20Singer"&gt;Bryan Singer&lt;/a&gt;, who also did the first two &lt;a href="w%3AX-Men"&gt;X-Men&lt;/a&gt; films. Superman is played by &lt;a href="w%3ABrandon%20Routh"&gt;Brandon Routh&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="w%3ALois%20Lane"&gt;Lois Lane&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href="w%3AKate%20Bosworth"&gt;Kate Bosworth&lt;/a&gt;, with &lt;a href="w%3ALex%20Luthor"&gt;Lex Luthor&lt;/a&gt; played by &lt;a href="w%3AKevin%20Spacey"&gt;Kevin Spacey&lt;/a&gt;. It is the first Superman film since 1987's ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3ASuperman%20IV%3A%20The%20Quest%20for%20Peace"&gt;Superman IV: The Quest for Peace&lt;/a&gt;♡❤.
&lt;br style="clear:both;"&gt;

