<doc id="44309" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=44309" title="All Ferrari front row on 2006 United States Grand Prix">
<h1>All Ferrari front row on 2006 United States Grand Prix</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=All%20Ferrari%20front%20row%20on%202006%20United%20States%20Grand%20Prix&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

Ferrari driver &lt;a href="w%3AMichael%20Schumacher"&gt;Michael Schumacher&lt;/a&gt; and his teammate &lt;a href="w%3AFelipe%20Massa"&gt;Felipe Massa&lt;/a&gt; won the front row on the &lt;a href="w%3AFIA"&gt;FIA&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3AFormula-1"&gt;Formula-1&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3A2006%20United%20States%20Grand%20Prix"&gt;United States Grand Prix&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href="w%3AIndianapolis%20Motor%20Speedway"&gt;Indianapolis Motor Speedway&lt;/a&gt;. 

&lt;a href="w%3ARenault"&gt;Renault&lt;/a&gt; driver &lt;a href="w%3AGiancarlo%20Fisichella"&gt;Giancarlo Fisicella&lt;/a&gt; qualified third. &lt;a href="w%3ARubens%20Barrichello"&gt;Rubens Barrichello&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3AHonda%20F1"&gt;Honda&lt;/a&gt; driver, wedged between the Renault cars on the starting grid and oust &lt;a href="w%3AFernando%20Alonso"&gt;Fernando Alonso&lt;/a&gt; to the fifth place.

A very successful qualification for the only American driver &lt;a href="w%3AScott%20Speed"&gt;Scott Speed&lt;/a&gt;, showed thirteenth result and for both &lt;a href="w%3AMidland%20F1%20Racing"&gt;MF1&lt;/a&gt;-&lt;a href="w%3AToyota%20Motor%20Corporation"&gt;Toyota&lt;/a&gt; team drivers, &lt;a href="w%3AChristijan%20Albers"&gt;Christijan Albers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3ATiago%20Monteiro"&gt;Tiago Monteiro&lt;/a&gt;, right after Speed.

