<doc id="45275" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=45275" title="News briefs:July 15, 2006">
<h1>News briefs:July 15, 2006</h1>
The time is 18:00 (UTC) on July 15th, 2006, and this is Audio Wikinews News Briefs.
<h2>Headlines</h2>
<h3>&lt;a href="Hezbollah-Israel%20conflict%20continues%2C%20Israel%20ultimatum%20to%20Syria"&gt;Hezbollah-Israel conflict continues, Israel ultimatum to Syria&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

Lebanon

As the conflict goes into its fourth day, Israel launches more air strikes against targets in Lebanon. Israel has also given Syria a 72 hour ultimatum to stop the Hezbollah attacks that continued to injure civilians in northern Israel and release the soldiers they claim were kidnapped.
<h3>&lt;a href="Suicide%20bomber%20assassinates%20prominent%20Shia%20cleric%20in%20Karachi%2C%20Pakistan"&gt;Suicide bomber assassinates prominent Shia cleric in Karachi, Pakistan&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

Pakistan

A suicide attacker detonated a bomb near the home of a prominent Pakistani Shia Muslim cleric in Karachi yesterday, killing the cleric and two other people, police said.
<h3>&lt;a href="Australia%20thrash%20South%20Africa%20in%20Tri%20Nations%20rugby%20match"&gt;Australia thrash South Africa in Tri Nations rugby match&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

sports - rugby

Australia has bounced back from their 12-32 loss against the All Blacks a week ago, to defeat the South African Springboks 49-0 in the second round of the 2006 Tri Nations rugby union series.
<h2>Closing statements</h2>

We invite you to visit wikinews.org for up-to-date news and information. This has been Audio Wikinews Newsbriefs. Thank you for listening, and enjoy the rest of your day.
