<doc id="45742" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=45742" title="JetBlue launches service from Raleigh, North Carolina to New York">
<h1>JetBlue launches service from Raleigh, North Carolina to New York</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=JetBlue%20launches%20service%20from%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina%20to%20New%20York&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;a href="w%3AJetBlue%20Airways"&gt;JetBlue Airways&lt;/a&gt; launched service from &lt;a href="w%3ARaleigh-Durham%20International%20Airport"&gt;Raleigh-Durham International Airport&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href="w%3AJohn%20F.%20Kennedy%20International%20Airport"&gt;John F. Kennedy International Airport&lt;/a&gt; on Thursday, July 20. The airline also announced daily service from &lt;a href="w%3ARaleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina"&gt;Raleigh&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href="w%3ABoston%2C%20Massachusetts"&gt;Boston&lt;/a&gt; starting on October 18.

JetBlue's service in Raleigh is comprised of four daily flights to New York, the airline's hub.

The route is flown by &lt;a href="w%3AEmbraer%20E-Jets"&gt;EMBRAER 190&lt;/a&gt; aircraft with a capacity of 100 passengers. The aircraft are equipped with &lt;a href="w%3ADirecTV"&gt;DirecTV&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3AXM%20Satellite%20Radio"&gt;XM Satellite Radio&lt;/a&gt; programming.

On October 18, JetBlue's service from Raleigh to Boston will begin with one daily flight.

&lt;a href="w%3ARaleigh-Durham%2C%20North%20Carolina"&gt;Raleigh-Durham&lt;/a&gt; International Airport currently has 223 daily departures to 37 cities.

