<h1>News briefs:July 24, 2006</h1>
The time is 22:00 (UTC) on July 24th, 2006, and this is Audio Wikinews News Briefs.
<h2>Headlines</h2>
<h3>&lt;a href="Lebanon%20faces%20humanitarian%20crisis"&gt;Lebanon faces humanitarian crisis&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

Lebanon

More than half a million people have been displaced in Lebanon as the conflict between Israel and Hezbollah continues into its second week. 
<h3>&lt;a href="PCC%20promotes%20new%20wave%20of%20attacks%20in%20Brazil"&gt;PCC promotes new wave of attacks in Brazil&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

Brazil

The criminal organization known as PCC (Primeiro Comando da Capital, Portuguese for First Command of the Capital City) promotes a new wave of attacks against civil and authority targets in Brazil which began early July. The main attacks are occurring in São Paulo state.
<h3>&lt;a href="Atlantis%20departs%20hangar%20ahead%20of%20August%2028%20launch"&gt;Atlantis departs hangar ahead of August 28 launch&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

United States

The Space Shuttle Atlantis has entered final preparation for mission STS-115, and has begun movement from its hangar at the Orbiter Processing Facility , to the Vehicle Assembly Building , where it will be attached to its external tank and solid rocket boosters. 
<h3>&lt;a href="Two%20New%20Zealand%20children%20die%20in%20fire"&gt;Two New Zealand children die in fire&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

New Zealand

Two children living in a small holiday home in Motueka, New Zealand died in a fire on Saturday night.
<h3>&lt;a href="Victoria%20Cross%20fetches%20record%20price%20at%20auction"&gt;Victoria Cross fetches record price at auction&lt;/a&gt;</h3>

Australia

The auction house Bonhams and Goodman have sold the last privately owned Victoria Cross awarded at the World War I, to Gallipoli campaign in Sydney tonight.
